The '''1993 Gerry Weber Open''' was a [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Tennis court#Grass courts|outdoor grass courts]]. It was the 1st edition of the [[Gerry Weber Open]], and was part of the [[ATP International Series|World Series]] of the [[1993 ATP Tour]]. It took place at the [[Gerry Weber Stadion]] in [[Halle, North Rhine-Westphalia]], [[Germany]], from June 14 through June 21, 1993.

==Champions==
===Singles===
{{main|1993 Gerry Weber Open <U+2013> Singles}}
'''{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Henri Leconte]]''' defeated {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Andrei Medvedev]] 6<U+2013>2, 6<U+2013>3
*It was Leconte's first title of the year, and the 20th of his career. 

===Doubles===
{{main|1993 Gerry Weber Open <U+2013> Doubles}}
{{flagicon|CZE}} '''[[Petr Korda]]''' / {{flagicon|CZE}} '''[[Cyril Suk]]''' defeated {{flagicon|USA}} [[Mike Bauer]] /{{flagicon|GER}} [[Marc-Kevin Goellner]] 7<U+2013>6, 5<U+2013>7 6<U+2013>3
*It was Korda's 2nd title of the year and the 13th of his career. It was Suk's first title of the year and the 7th of his career.

